1-Both servers":Install openssh-server
sudo yum -y install openssh-server

2-Server1: Generate private/public rsa key pair
ssh-keygen -t rsa

3-Go to directory .ssh/
cd .ssh/
.ssh$ ls
The files id_rsa(private key) and id_rsa.pub(public key) are created. 

4-Change id_rsa.pub to authorized_keys.
.ssh$ cp id_rsa.pub authorized_keys

5-Change permissions:
.ssh$ chmod 600 authorized_keys


6-Go to home directory:
.ssh$ cd 
~$

7-Copy your Public Key
(ssh-copy-id username@remote_host_ip)
~$ ssh-copy-id vagrant@192.168.1.8

8-Server2:
Go to .ssh directory
.ssh$ ls
authorized_keys file is created 

9-Server1: Go to .ssh
.ssh$ open id_rsa and copy the content.

10-Server2: go to .ssh directory and paste the private key content on a file named id_rsa.
.ssh$ vi id_rsa
Paste the content and save.

11-Change permissions:
.ssh$ chmod 600 id_rsa

12-Now you can log into the remote host without the remote account's password:
server1 ~$ ssh server2
